Comment:
Paramount recently said they won't make a third TMNT film so I thought I'd share my ideas for a reboot trilogy:

Film 1: have the first half focus on the turtles taking out Stockman and his mouser robots with aid from April (who worked for stockman like in the comic), the second half have the turtles find out about the Foot and Shredder, ending with the rooftop battle like the original comic. 

Film 2: The turtles help vigilante Casey Jones take out the Purple Dragons led by Hun (who secretly works for Shredder just like Stockman) the the second half adapts the Shredder Strikes Back storyline; Leo's ambush by the Foot Elite and the attack/fire at April's apartment, Shredder aided by the recently mutated Bebop and Rocksteady (not as incompetent as the show). 

Film 3: Adapts the Return to New York storyline: the first third deals with Leo's recovery, then the assault on Shredder's lair, the turtles face the Elite, Bebop and Rocksteady, Hun and the recently mutated Baxter Fly. The final battle is between Shredder and Leo while the others fight the mutants, ending with Shredder's decapitation. 

Just an idea though

Comment: Cards on the table now, this movie looked pretty bad when I saw the trailer, but when I saw the movie, I ended up really liking it and being entertained by it. It has flaws that I can willingly say are there, but it's just nonstop silliness and goofiness that it rolls with, making it much more entertaining, and never taking itself seriously. Like a 2 hour episode of the original show, bringing all the characters (Bebop and Rocksteady, Krang, and Casey Jones) and throwing them together in a blender. So if you do go see the movie, do not expect seriousness or realism. Just go in there for 2 hours of entertaining comedy and action.

Title: Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles: Out of the Shadows Official Trailer #1 (2016) - Megan Fox Movie HD
Comment: Awesome!!!!!!!! So it only took 30 years or so for the fans' voices to be heard - we finally get Krang, Rocksteady, and Bebop in a live-action version of TMNT! And they're even throwing Casey Jones in as well, so even more of the old original stuff is making a debut (I know we had Casey in the old 90s films, but the third one was so wtf-worthy, and again, lack of the aforementioned mutants). Roll out the pizzas! That Turtle Van is badass. I prefer the old original look of the turtles, but lots of things are making up for their weird looks (particularly Donatello; we've known since 1984 that he's the smart one, so the geek glasses and heavy-gear backpack weren't necessary). Question though - is it necessary for April to show so much skin? She didn't do that in the original...just because Michael Bay has a constant hard-on for her isn't an excuse. >.< Still not content with her in that role, but hey, this looks awesome! Excuse me while I go pre-order tickets!

Comment: WAIT JUST A MINUTE, "Out of the Shadows"? They named it after the 2013 video game based on the 2012 TV series? That's what I would've preferred the first movie to have been about. I thought they were going to just simply name it "Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles 2". And the Turtles are going to reveal themselves to the public and Baxter Stockman and Bebop and Rocksteady are going to make their very first big screen appearance? That just blew my mind away. I wish my dad was still around to see this. He liked Bebop and Rocksteady. And the Turtles' newest vehicle at 2:10 looks better than the van that was shown at the end of the first movie. It reminds me of the hauler vehicle that was first shown of the Back To The Sewer episodes of season 7 of the Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles 2003-2009 animated series http://farm4.staticflickr.com/3014/2873375994_731362205a.jpg. I would've preferred a realistic version of the shellraiser vehicle and I also would've preferred doing the Triceraton invasion of the sequel just like of the last episode "Annihilation Earth!"of season 3 of the 2012 series.
